# FSTEC — security controls

Platform for tracking FSTEC security measures across subsidiaries (ДЗО). Public assignment links + admin panel.

## Required controls

| Control | Implementation |
|---------|----------------|
| Admin access | iron-session cookie; `SESSION_SECRET` ≥ 32 chars; middleware on `/admin/*` |
| Public access | Unguessable `access_links.token`; optional `expiresAt`; `revokedAt` |
| Rate limiting | `lib/public/rate-limit.ts` on public API |
| Secrets | `.env.local` only; `.env.example` without values |
| Database | PostgreSQL via Docker; never commit dumps with PII |
| HTTPS | Required in production |

## Skepticism checklist

- Public routes must not expose admin data or unscoped order items.
- Token must scope to single order + organization.
- Do not log passwords or session secrets.
- Validate all public write endpoints against active token.

## Verify

- Grep diff for `password` in console.log — reject.
- Confirm `.env.local` not in git status before commit.
- curl revoked/expired token → 404.
